<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
    <body>
        <p>Open Telemetry monitoring only allows client requests from known predefined IP addresses. You can add and remove addresses from the list of known addresses. Commit your changes for them to take effect.</p>
        <h4>To add an IP address:</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>Enter <span class="userinput">a</span> to add an address.</li>
            <li>Enter a fully qualified IPv4 address or CIDR&#160;address (for example, 192.168.1.19).</li>
        </ol>
        <h4>To delete an IP address:</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>Enter <span class="userinput">d</span> to delete an entry.</li>
            <li>Use the arrow keys to select an entry to delete.</li>
            <li>Confirm the deletion.</li>
        </ol>
        <h4>To commit your IP address changes:</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>Enter <span class="userinput">c</span> to commit your changes, which include any pending additions or deletions.</li>
            <li>Enter <span class="userinput">x</span> to return to the previous menu.</li>
        </ol>
    </body>
</html>